<div id="page-container">
      <div id="content-wrap">
        
        <div id="header" class="header">
          <div class="header__left">
            <p>Mousehunt Collector</p>
          </div>
          <div class="header__right">
            <% if current_user %>
              <div class="welcome-container">
                <div class="welcome-message">Welcome, </div>
                <div class="welcome-name"><%= link_to  current_user.name, user_path(current_user) %> </div>
              </div>
              <div class="logout-container">
                <form action="<%= session_path %>" method="post">
                  <input type="hidden" name="authenticity_token" value="<%= form_authenticity_token %>">
                  <input type="hidden" name="_method" value="delete">
                  <input type="submit" value="Logout">
                </form>
              </div>
            <% else %>
              <%= link_to  "Sign in", new_session_url%>
              <%= link_to  "Sign up", new_user_path %>
            <% end %>
          </div>
        </div>
      
        <div id="content-body">
          <div class="main">
  <h3>Welcome to Mousehunt Collector</h3>
  <p>This app is designed as a companion to players of the game <%= link_to  "Mousehunt", "https://www.mousehuntgame.com" %>, which is also available on Facebook. Having been a slow but steady player over the last 9 years, I decided it was time to put away my excel spreadsheet and develop a better inventory acquisition tracker.
  <p>This is a place to search and review all of the available Weapons, Bases, and other collectible items needed to play the game. If you'd like a better understanding, please see the <%= link_to  "MH Wiki", "https://mhwiki.hitgrab.com/wiki/index.php/MouseHunt_Wiki" %>
  <br>
  <br>
  <br>

  <%= link_to  "Ranks", ranks_path %><br>
  <%= link_to  "Regions", regions_path %><br>
  <%= link_to  "Locations", locations_path %><br>
  <%= link_to  "Mice", mice_path %><br>
  <%= link_to  "Items", items_path %>

  <br>
  <br>
  <br>
    <p>Items add/edit forms now category specific and have stats on the same model</p>

</div>

        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div id="footer" class="footer-content">
        <small>Copyright Â© 2020 Christina Kiesz</small><%= link_to  "Back to Main", root_path %><%= link_to  "Source code on Github", 'https://github.com/ck4adventure/mhdb' %>
      </div>
    </div>










